SeaChange International, Inc.

50 Nagog Park 
Acton MA 01720 United States
Phone: +1 978-___-____
Fax: +1 978-___-____
http://www.schange.com





12
Managers




60
IT employees




$12.2MEST.
IT Budget




SeaChange International provides hardware and software solutions for the broadcast/telecommunications industry. Head quarters in Acton, SeaChange International has product development, sales, support offices across the globe.
The IT department at SeaChange International is based out of the corporate offices in Acton, MA. The Vice president and Chief Architect is responsible for all aspects of technology, including the high-level architectural designing, construction, reconstruction, standardization, and modernization of the… MoreThe IT department at SeaChange International is based out of the corporate offices in Acton, MA. The Vice president and Chief Architect is responsible for all aspects of technology, including the high-level architectural designing, construction, reconstruction, standardization, and modernization of the company's platform. Another vice president is responsible for all the technical aspects at the company, he develops strategic planning and provides direction and control for product development activities.

That director is responsible for overall internal infrastructure operations, which includes enterprise telecommunications, LAN/WAN operations, and information security.

A program manager develops project implementation plans with the customers & internal teams for planning, installation, system integration, data migration, etc. from project commencement to industry service live.

A separate applications group handles development of the company's financial systems in Oracle. That group also includes Web development, which entails the corporate website, enterprise Intranet, and SharePoint development.

Other groups are responsible for upkeep, support and further development of the company's client-side services. That includes the infrastructure supporting content delivery and development of applications that function on various platforms.





