SeaChange International, Inc. Key Developments

SeaChange International, Inc. Announces Resignation of Olson as Director
Jul 18 17
The Board of Directors of SeaChange International, Inc. has accepted the resignation of Mr. Olson as a director, effective July 18, 2017.


SeaChange International, Inc. Reports Unaudited Consolidated Earnings Results for the First Quarter Ended April 30, 2017; Provides Earnings Guidance for Second Quarter and Full Year of Fiscal 2018
Jun 6 17
SeaChange International, Inc. reported unaudited consolidated earnings results for the first quarter ended April 30, 2017. For the quarter, the company reported total revenues of $16,667,000 compared to $21,570,000 a year ago. Loss from operations was $5,468,000 compared to $9,575,000 a year ago. Loss before income taxes was $5,102,000 compared to $8,653,000 a year ago. Net loss was $5,371,000 or $0.15 per basic and diluted share compared to $8,907,000 or $0.26 per basic and diluted share a year ago. Total cash used in operating activities was $917,000 compared to $5,486,000 a year ago. Purchases of property and equipment were $196,000 compared to $159,000 a year ago. The non-GAAP loss from operations was $1.7 million, or $0.05 per basic share, compared to $6.8 million, or $0.20 per share. 

The company provided earnings guidance for second quarter and full year of fiscal 2018. For the quarter, the company anticipates revenue to be in the range of $17 million to $20 million, U.S. GAAP loss from operations to be in the range of $0.13 to $0.07 per basic share, and non-GAAP loss from operations to be in the range of $0.09 to $0.03 per basic share.  

For full fiscal 2018, the company anticipates revenue to be in the range of $80 million to $90 million, U.S. GAAP loss from operations to be in the range of $0.37 to $0.25 per basic share and non-GAAP operating income to be in the range of a loss of $0.10 per basic share to income of $0.02 per diluted share.


SeaChange International, Inc., Annual General Meeting, Jul 13, 2017
May 26 17
SeaChange International, Inc., Annual General Meeting, Jul 13, 2017, at 09:00 US Eastern Standard Time. Location: 50 Nagog Park, Acton Massachusetts United States Agenda: To elect the nominees named in the proxy statement to the Board of Directors to serve for three-year terms as Class III Directors; to conduct an advisory vote on the compensation of the Company's named executive officers; to conduct an advisory vote of the frequency of the shareholder advisory vote on the compensation of the Company's named executive officers; to approve an amendment to the Company's Second Amended and Restated 2011 Compensation and Incentive Plan; to ratify the appointment of the Company's independent registered public accounting firm; and to transact such other business as may properly come before the meeting and any adjournments thereof.


